U.K. Car Insurers Had Losses of $3.2 Billion in 2010, FT Reports

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-06-17T01:24:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-17/u-k-car-insurers-had-losses-of-3-2-billion-in-2010-ft-reports.html
U.K. car insurers incurred losses of
more than 2 billion pounds ($3.2 billion) in 2010 as the
industry faced an increase in claims, particularly for bodily
injury, the Financial Times reported, citing analysis by
Deloitte & Touche LLP.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 